-- Global Funds Buy Net 4.6 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2012-05-21T03:29:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/global-funds-buy-net-4-6-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors  bought a  net 4.6
billion rupees ($84.4 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
May 18, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1 percent to 787.2 billion rupees, or 32.2
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds sold a net 2.49 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on May 18, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
